canonical:
  title: 謝朝叅次客省幕賜酒食衣對表
  author: 金克己
  language: lzh
  text: 執玉帝庭親覩淸光之肅穆張筵賓幕猥加異數之便番揣分非宜捫心是懼中謝 陪臣遠從日域來覲天京方趨朝海之聯遽沐漏泉之澤華紳粲服吉兮燠兮異果芳醪多矣嘉矣顧難報效但切銘藏
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 謝朝叅次客省幕賜酒食衣對表
  author: 金克己
  language: lzh
  text: 執玉帝庭。親覩淸光之肅穆。張筵賓幕。猥加異數之便番。揣分非宜。捫心是懼。中謝。 陪臣遠從日域。來覲天京。方趨朝海之聯。遽沐漏泉之澤。華紳粲服。吉兮燠兮。異果芳醪。多矣嘉矣。顧難報效。但切銘藏。
korean:
  title: 조회에 참예했다가 객성막에 들렸을 때 술과 음식과 옷을 하사하심을 사례하는 표
  author: 김극기
  language: kor
  text: |-
    대궐 뜰에 옥(玉)을 잡아 친히 거룩한 용안을 뵈옵고 빈관(賓館)에 연석을 차리어 외람되이 이수(異數)의 접대를 받자오니, 분수에 넘치는 영광에 가슴을 만지며 두려워하옵나이다. 중사(中謝)
    배신이 멀리 해뜨는 고장에서부터 천자의 서울에 와서 뵈옵고, 바야흐로 바다에 조종(朝宗)하는 반열(班列)에 추창하옴에 문득 샘물같이 솟는 은택에 목욕하였나이다. 화려한 큰 띠에 찬란한 예복 차림으로 줄을 지어 늘어선 곳에, 진기한 실과와 향기로운 술이 푸짐하고 아름답사오니, 이 은혜를 보답하옵기 어렵사옴에 오직 정성을 다할 생각만 간절할 뿐이옵니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0380_010_0280&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Memorial of Gratitude for Wine, Food, and Robes Presented at the Guest Pavilion During Court Audience
  author: Kim Geuk-gi
  language: eng
  text: |-
    In the imperial courtyard, I grasped the jade scepter and witnessed firsthand the solemn radiance of your countenance. In the guest pavilion, a grand feast was laid before me, and I received exceptional honors beyond my station. My heart trembles at this undeserved glory, and I am seized with reverent awe.

    Your servant traveled from distant eastern lands to pay court at the celestial capital. Just as I took my place among the tributary ranks that flow to the sea, I was suddenly bathed in grace as plentiful as spring waters. In robes of crimson silk and official regalia that gleam with brilliance, surrounded by rare delicacies and fragrant wines, I stand overwhelmed. How can such bounty be repaid? Yet my devotion shall remain steadfast and eternal in my heart.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'jade scepter' (玉) refers to the formal protocol of court audience where officials hold symbolic insignia.
  - key: ''
    value: The imagery of 'flowing to the sea' (朝宗) is a classical metaphor for tributary states paying homage to the central empire.
  - key: ''
    value: This memorial represents the formal gratitude expected from Korean envoys receiving imperial hospitality during official court visits to China.
